ist.remove(key: \"mykey\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Drivers","text":"Drivers","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"persist"},{"text":" framework defines an API for storing key\/value pairs. You also need a driver for the framework. When configuring your application if you want to use ","type":"text"},{"code":"persist","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" you have to add it to the application and indicate what driver you are going to use. ","type":"text"},{"code":"Hummingbird","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" comes with a memory based driver which will store these values in the memory of your server."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let persist = MemoryPersistDriver()"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you use the memory based driver the key\/value pairs you store will be lost if your server goes down, also you will not be able to share values between server processes."}]},{"text":"Redis","level":3,"anchor":"Redis","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use Redis to store the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"persists"},{"type":"text","text":" key\/value pairs with the "},{"code":"HummingbirdRedis","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" library. You would setup ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"persist"},{"text":" to use Redis as follows. To use the Redis driver you need to have setup Redis with Hummingbird as well.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let redis = RedisConnectionPoolService(","    .init(hostname: redisHostname, port: 6379), ","    logger: Logger(label: \"Redis\")",")","let persist = RedisPersistDriver(redisConnectionPoolService: redis)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"level":3,"text":"Fluent","type":"heading","anchor":"Fluent"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.opticalaberration.hummingbird\/documentation\/Hu